## Part 4: Critical Rules

### Do's
| Rule | Why |
|------|-----|
| Subject: lowercase, 3-5 words | Looks personal, not marketing |
| Under 75 words | Respect their time, mobile-friendly |
| ONE CTA only | Don't overwhelm |
| Include both links | tedca.org + cal.com |
| Connect observation to $$ | Make the pain tangible |

### Don'ts
| Avoid | Why |
|-------|-----|
| "I hope you are well" | Wastes preview text |
| False urgency ("last chance!") | Triggers spam filters |
| Flattery ("impressive legacy!") | Feels generic |
| Multiple questions | Reduces response rate |
| Long paragraphs | Lost on mobile |

---

## Part 5: Follow-Up Sequence

- **Day 1:** Initial email (use trigger-based template)
- **Day 3:** Short bump with stat
  - "Hey [Name], quick follow-up. Did you know voicemail has a 93% failure rate? Demo at tedca.org"
- **Day 7:** Case study angle
  - "Hey [Name], just helped another [City] contractor recover $4K/month in missed calls. tedca.org"
- **Day 14:** Break-up email
  - "Hey [Name], I'll assume timing isn't right. If call handling ever becomes a priority, I'm at tedca.org"

